metadata.name: Shower Thoughts
metadata.description:
Where do you go to safely and openly hold your grief? 
Who do you allow to witness your sadness?  
When do you have eyes to see it's out of your hands?

I could share peculiar and personal experiences that drove the creation of this piece...

However, I just want to welcome an open space for others to reflect on these questions that frequent my mind. 
 
Thank you humans.

Love,

Potato

24 in x 30 in. Acrylic on canvas.
